1
00:00:00,459 --> 00:00:02,289
In the previous episode,

2
00:00:02,406 --> 00:00:04,486
Nankatsu faced
the difficult team

3
00:00:04,511 --> 00:00:05,616
from Shimizu.

4
00:00:06,421 --> 00:00:09,211
Right from the beginning,
Tsubasa was marked

5
00:00:09,236 --> 00:00:11,076
by orders of
the opposite team's captain,

6
00:00:11,196 --> 00:00:12,656
preventing him
from doing anything.

7
00:00:12,656 --> 00:00:14,866
On the other side,
Wakabayashi received

8
00:00:14,891 --> 00:00:16,826
a direct hit
on his injured leg

9
00:00:16,851 --> 00:00:18,786
making him unable
to move freely.

10
00:00:18,811 --> 00:00:21,731
It was a hard blow
to our beloved goal keeper.

11
00:00:22,005 --> 00:00:23,841
Despite all the odds,

12
00:00:23,866 --> 00:00:25,576
all the members
from Nankatsu

13
00:00:25,601 --> 00:00:28,091
did their best to clear
the way for Tsubasa,

14
00:00:28,116 --> 00:00:31,036
allowing him to score
a goal against Shimizu.

15
00:00:32,140 --> 00:00:35,576
At the end, Nankatsu
managed to win the match

16
00:00:35,696 --> 00:00:37,131
and now,
they will be representing

17
00:00:37,156 --> 00:00:39,736
the Shizuoka Prefecture
in the national tournament!

18
00:00:41,351 --> 00:00:43,761
No, Tsubasa!
It's not ready yet!

19
00:00:43,786 --> 00:00:44,946
-Ow!
-Easy!

20
00:00:45,203 --> 00:00:46,528
It'll be ready soon,

21
00:00:46,632 --> 00:00:48,672
so go and take
your bath now.

22
00:00:48,736 --> 00:00:51,656
But Mom, I'm really hungry.
Let me have some.

23
00:00:51,681 --> 00:00:53,011
Ugh!
What a stubborn kid!

24
00:00:53,036 --> 00:00:55,009
This is a typical day
in the Ozora family.

25
00:00:55,034 --> 00:00:57,837
The captain, his wife
and Tsubasa.

26
00:00:58,298 --> 00:01:01,286
This is a warm happy family.

27
00:01:02,149 --> 00:01:04,736
But even if the three
of them agreed...

28
00:01:04,736 --> 00:01:07,116
will it be really okay
to take Tsubasa

29
00:01:07,141 --> 00:01:08,641
with me to Brazil?

30
00:01:08,996 --> 00:01:10,906
A family must stay united.

31
00:01:11,470 --> 00:01:12,921
If I take Tsubasa,

32
00:01:12,946 --> 00:01:15,656
then I'll be the one
tearing them apart.

33
00:01:15,681 --> 00:01:17,061
-Roberto...
-Oh!

34
00:01:18,148 --> 00:01:19,148
What's the matter?

35
00:01:19,775 --> 00:01:21,575
I'm all right.

36
00:01:21,735 --> 00:01:22,735
Okay then.

37
00:01:26,975 --> 00:01:32,065
[opening theme]

38
00:03:09,602 --> 00:03:12,812
Episode 13:
The National Tournament Begins!

39
00:03:13,245 --> 00:03:15,575
SIXTH JUVENILE NATIONAL TOURNAMENT HOKKAIDO FINAL

40
00:03:17,184 --> 00:03:19,174
Hey, what are you doing,
Sapporo?!

41
00:03:19,199 --> 00:03:20,510
Go get the ball!

42
00:03:20,535 --> 00:03:22,509
There's only
one minute left!

43
00:03:23,368 --> 00:03:23,948
Captain!

44
00:03:24,002 --> 00:03:25,332
The Sapporo team attacks

45
00:03:25,357 --> 00:03:27,687
with numerous players,
but can't get the ball!

46
00:03:27,712 --> 00:03:29,042
Captain Hikaru Matsuyama

47
00:03:29,067 --> 00:03:30,752
from the Furano team
controls the ball!

48
00:03:30,872 --> 00:03:32,502
You won't get the ball!

49
00:03:32,834 --> 00:03:34,467
Oh no!

50
00:03:35,767 --> 00:03:37,057
Ah!

51
00:03:37,082 --> 00:03:38,422
This guy is so annoying!

52
00:03:38,447 --> 00:03:40,227
Get the ball
away from him now!

53
00:03:40,252 --> 00:03:41,697
Captain!
Make a pass!

54
00:03:41,736 --> 00:03:42,516
No, he can't!

55
00:03:42,541 --> 00:03:44,359
The captain is
completely surrounded!

56
00:03:44,384 --> 00:03:45,254
What do we do?

57
00:03:45,434 --> 00:03:48,459
Hikaru
Matsuyama keeps the ball!

58
00:03:48,484 --> 00:03:51,024
Can he get away from
the opposing team!?

59
00:03:51,354 --> 00:03:53,564
And now,
we're in over time!

60
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:56,434
Given this situation,
it looks like our favorite,

61
00:03:56,434 --> 00:03:58,064
the Sapporo, will lose.

62
00:03:58,089 --> 00:04:00,774
Come on, Furano!
Just a little bit more!

63
00:04:01,484 --> 00:04:03,814
Captain, hang in
there a little bit more!

64
00:04:06,774 --> 00:04:07,484
-Ah!
-Ah!

65
00:04:07,604 --> 00:04:10,484
And the referee signals
the end of the game!

66
00:04:10,604 --> 00:04:13,434
Yeah! We did it!

67
00:04:14,034 --> 00:04:15,264
Impressive!

68
00:04:15,713 --> 00:04:19,003
The famous Sapporo team
has lost to the Furano team!

69
00:04:19,688 --> 00:04:20,858
Now the Furano team

70
00:04:20,970 --> 00:04:22,930
will move on to
the National Tournament!

71
00:04:22,955 --> 00:04:25,415
Despite the adversities
and all thanks to

72
00:04:25,726 --> 00:04:28,961
its Captain,
Hikaru Matsuyama!

73
00:04:29,094 --> 00:04:32,714
The team managed
an incredible victory!

74
00:04:33,484 --> 00:04:35,184
We were able to
win this game!

75
00:04:35,209 --> 00:04:36,669
And we did it
without Misaki.

76
00:04:36,827 --> 00:04:37,827
Yeah!

77
00:04:38,234 --> 00:04:39,434
We'll go to
the National Tournament

78
00:04:39,564 --> 00:04:40,644
and we'll complete
against him!

79
00:04:40,774 --> 00:04:41,774
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

80
00:04:42,695 --> 00:04:43,985
We did it, Misaki.

81
00:04:44,775 --> 00:04:46,040
I can't wait
to play against you

82
00:04:46,065 --> 00:04:47,275
in the national tournament.

83
00:04:55,604 --> 00:04:57,234
MISAKI

84
00:04:58,944 --> 00:05:00,024
Are you done, Dad?

85
00:05:00,049 --> 00:05:01,049
Tell me...

86
00:05:01,394 --> 00:05:03,274
will we go
somewhere else now?

87
00:05:03,774 --> 00:05:04,774
Yes.

88
00:05:05,144 --> 00:05:06,144
Hm...

89
00:05:06,765 --> 00:05:08,318
Once the national
tournament

90
00:05:08,343 --> 00:05:09,463
and the semester end,

91
00:05:09,488 --> 00:05:11,308
you'll have to transfer
to another school.

92
00:05:11,794 --> 00:05:13,354
You should tell
your friends.

93
00:05:13,774 --> 00:05:14,774
Sure, Dad.

94
00:05:21,833 --> 00:05:22,934
I'm sorry, but I think

95
00:05:22,959 --> 00:05:24,749
you should forget about
the national tournament.

96
00:05:24,953 --> 00:05:27,073
-But doctor!
-Genzo, please calm down!

97
00:05:27,389 --> 00:05:28,049
Listen, Genzo,

98
00:05:28,074 --> 00:05:29,824
you have a bright future
ahead of you.

99
00:05:30,104 --> 00:05:31,274
Don't risk it like that.

100
00:05:31,299 --> 00:05:32,909
If you go into
the tournament,

101
00:05:32,934 --> 00:05:35,099
your injury will
only get worse.

102
00:05:35,524 --> 00:05:38,604
The best is to wait for it
to heal completely.

103
00:05:38,836 --> 00:05:40,126
He's right, Genzo.

104
00:05:40,312 --> 00:05:42,142
You shouldn't risk
your whole future for this.

105
00:05:42,167 --> 00:05:43,547
Please try to understand.

106
00:05:44,234 --> 00:05:45,234
But it's just that...

107
00:05:45,883 --> 00:05:47,503
that I made a promise
to someone

108
00:05:47,528 --> 00:05:49,318
and I must do my part
as well.

109
00:05:51,084 --> 00:05:52,394
I'm sorry,
but Master Genzo

110
00:05:52,419 --> 00:05:53,469
is not home right now.

111
00:05:54,274 --> 00:05:55,749
She says
the captain is not home.

112
00:05:55,774 --> 00:05:56,814
What now?

113
00:05:56,839 --> 00:05:59,564
I wonder if the captain got
better from that injury.

114
00:05:59,774 --> 00:06:01,234
I sure hope so.

115
00:06:01,259 --> 00:06:02,839
He must get better soon,

116
00:06:02,993 --> 00:06:05,548
so we can all play in
the national tournament.

117
00:06:05,947 --> 00:06:08,367
Don't worry, I'm sure
we will win the tournament.

118
00:06:08,894 --> 00:06:09,894
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

119
00:06:10,884 --> 00:06:11,734
All right, Son,

120
00:06:11,854 --> 00:06:13,126
did you brush your teeth?

121
00:06:13,151 --> 00:06:15,150
I already did, Mom!

122
00:06:15,283 --> 00:06:16,524
Ugh...
Why do you treat me

123
00:06:16,549 --> 00:06:18,618
like one of your employees?
That's so annoying!

124
00:06:18,644 --> 00:06:20,934
Don't talk to me like that,
young man.

125
00:06:21,197 --> 00:06:22,774
You may have won
the try outs,

126
00:06:22,984 --> 00:06:25,604
but you've barely played
in the games!

127
00:06:25,629 --> 00:06:27,499
But what do you
want me to do, Mom?

128
00:06:27,524 --> 00:06:30,064
All my teammates
are really strong, you know?

129
00:06:30,184 --> 00:06:31,789
Well, that's why
I'm making you work,

130
00:06:31,814 --> 00:06:34,144
so you can become stronger
and you can get to play.

131
00:06:34,368 --> 00:06:35,868
Aw man!
And I thought I was

132
00:06:35,964 --> 00:06:38,014
gonna to take a break
these days.

133
00:06:38,367 --> 00:06:39,907
Why me?

134
00:06:40,997 --> 00:06:42,934
The members
from the Nankatsu team

135
00:06:43,064 --> 00:06:44,394
enjoy their last break

136
00:06:44,394 --> 00:06:46,604
before the national
tournament begins.

137
00:06:47,633 --> 00:06:49,213
Tsubasa,
on the other hand...

138
00:06:50,914 --> 00:06:51,914
Huh?

139
00:07:00,394 --> 00:07:02,024
What's wrong, Tsubasa?

140
00:07:02,049 --> 00:07:03,969
You can't take
that simple pass?

141
00:07:04,564 --> 00:07:05,984
I can, sorry!

142
00:07:07,854 --> 00:07:09,144
What's wrong
with Roberto?

143
00:07:09,274 --> 00:07:10,274
He's been...

144
00:07:10,774 --> 00:07:12,354
acting weird lately.

145
00:07:15,524 --> 00:07:16,524
Tsubasa...

146
00:07:16,854 --> 00:07:18,894
do you really want to
go to Brazil with me?

147
00:07:18,919 --> 00:07:19,919
Of course!

148
00:07:20,195 --> 00:07:21,355
Of course I want to go!

149
00:07:22,314 --> 00:07:23,854
If you come to Brazil
with me...

150
00:07:24,354 --> 00:07:26,354
your mom will be all alone.

151
00:07:26,777 --> 00:07:28,277
Even so,
do you still want to

152
00:07:28,302 --> 00:07:30,132
-go to Brazil with me?
-What?

153
00:07:30,814 --> 00:07:31,814
Again?

154
00:07:31,934 --> 00:07:34,564
I already told you, Roberto,
I do want to go.

155
00:07:35,894 --> 00:07:37,304
These last
couple of days...

156
00:07:38,173 --> 00:07:39,463
I've been thinking
that maybe

157
00:07:39,734 --> 00:07:42,234
I'm being selfish
and self-centered.

158
00:07:43,311 --> 00:07:46,181
That selfishness may break
that bond with your family.

159
00:07:46,206 --> 00:07:47,246
Roberto, stop it.

160
00:07:47,894 --> 00:07:48,956
It's not like that.

161
00:07:48,981 --> 00:07:51,141
I think it's best if...

162
00:07:51,644 --> 00:07:52,604
-Huh?
-Huh?

163
00:07:52,734 --> 00:07:53,734
Genzo!

164
00:07:54,350 --> 00:07:55,350
Can we talk?

165
00:07:55,684 --> 00:07:56,684
It's urgent...

166
00:07:57,438 --> 00:07:58,438
-Oh...
-Oh...

167
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:02,260
Tsubasa, I won't play
in the national tournament.

168
00:08:02,394 --> 00:08:03,394
What?!

169
00:08:03,604 --> 00:08:04,394
Uh...

170
00:08:04,524 --> 00:08:06,064
It looks like my injury

171
00:08:06,184 --> 00:08:07,814
is more serious
than I thought.

172
00:08:08,564 --> 00:08:10,684
I must wait until
it completely heals.

173
00:08:11,434 --> 00:08:12,894
And that's the reason why...

174
00:08:13,274 --> 00:08:14,734
I need you to do me a favor.

175
00:08:15,484 --> 00:08:16,564
Even if I'm not there,

176
00:08:16,723 --> 00:08:18,473
I want you to win
all the matches

177
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:19,498
in the tournament.

178
00:08:19,894 --> 00:08:22,144
Until you get to play
against Kojiro Hyuga.

179
00:08:22,274 --> 00:08:23,274
All the matches?

180
00:08:24,050 --> 00:08:26,184
I let him score
a goal that day.

181
00:08:26,314 --> 00:08:28,314
And I failed you
as a keeper and a captain.

182
00:08:28,854 --> 00:08:31,434
I'm sure I must have
my leg healed by then...

183
00:08:32,064 --> 00:08:33,394
I'm begging you...

184
00:08:33,484 --> 00:08:34,774
Please wait for me.

185
00:08:35,854 --> 00:08:37,064
Don't worry about it...

186
00:08:37,158 --> 00:08:39,118
You can count on us, Genzo.

187
00:08:44,104 --> 00:08:45,404
-Let's do it!
-Send it over here!

188
00:08:46,104 --> 00:08:46,774
Run!

189
00:08:46,894 --> 00:08:47,894
Got it!

190
00:08:48,394 --> 00:08:49,484
Yeah, one more!

191
00:08:50,314 --> 00:08:51,409
What's going on?

192
00:08:51,434 --> 00:08:52,854
Put more energy in it!

193
00:08:53,131 --> 00:08:54,881
If you can't stand
this heat,

194
00:08:55,104 --> 00:08:57,394
then you better forget
about winning the nationals!

195
00:08:57,394 --> 00:08:58,394
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

196
00:08:59,358 --> 00:09:02,058
It looks like the absence
of Genzo Wakabayashi

197
00:09:02,328 --> 00:09:04,328
is the cause of
their unusual behavior.

198
00:09:04,854 --> 00:09:07,099
-I know.
-It is to be expected.

199
00:09:07,124 --> 00:09:08,982
We have some kids
from the Shutetsu,

200
00:09:09,007 --> 00:09:12,302
without him,
they must be feeling down.

201
00:09:12,604 --> 00:09:15,394
It's true. Genzo is not only
the goal keeper,

202
00:09:15,394 --> 00:09:18,354
he's the captain that
keeps everyone focused.

203
00:09:18,984 --> 00:09:20,354
His absence is very strong

204
00:09:20,484 --> 00:09:22,394
and not having him for
the next matches...

205
00:09:22,734 --> 00:09:25,314
is really affecting
his teammates' spirits.

206
00:09:25,564 --> 00:09:28,812
The only one that looks
to be unaffected is Tsubasa.

207
00:09:28,837 --> 00:09:29,887
Heads up, Taro!

208
00:09:29,941 --> 00:09:31,210
A one-two!

209
00:09:31,235 --> 00:09:33,525
And Taro Misaki has always
been cool headed.

210
00:09:36,354 --> 00:09:37,754
Yeah! We did it!

211
00:09:38,244 --> 00:09:39,244
Idiot!

212
00:09:39,394 --> 00:09:41,144
Even I could've
stopped that!

213
00:09:41,274 --> 00:09:43,184
Genzo is not here now,
so you're the only one

214
00:09:43,314 --> 00:09:44,314
-Now even Ishizaki
-that we've got!

215
00:09:44,339 --> 00:09:45,339
-is strict.
-So put it together!

216
00:09:48,564 --> 00:09:50,604
I promised him that
I would win all matches,

217
00:09:50,734 --> 00:09:52,394
and I will keep
that promise.

218
00:09:58,394 --> 00:09:59,604
Miss Ozora...

219
00:10:00,024 --> 00:10:02,024
If your son
goes with me to Brazil,

220
00:10:02,314 --> 00:10:03,434
won't you be lonely?

221
00:10:03,950 --> 00:10:06,455
Huh?
Why are you so worried?

222
00:10:06,564 --> 00:10:08,644
Please, ma'am.
I need to know.

223
00:10:11,354 --> 00:10:12,354
The truth is...

224
00:10:12,484 --> 00:10:13,460
I would be lying
if I say that

225
00:10:13,485 --> 00:10:15,275
I won't get lonely
sometimes.

226
00:10:15,354 --> 00:10:16,854
But just like
I told my husband,

227
00:10:16,984 --> 00:10:18,434
we parents can't keep
our children

228
00:10:18,434 --> 00:10:20,004
from making their dreams
come true.

229
00:10:20,183 --> 00:10:22,813
But ma'am, Tsubasa
is only in elementary!

230
00:10:23,323 --> 00:10:24,323
I know...

231
00:10:24,348 --> 00:10:26,873
but my son is very mature
for his age.

232
00:10:27,739 --> 00:10:28,909
And his biggest dream
in the world

233
00:10:28,934 --> 00:10:31,064
is to become a professional
soccer player.

234
00:10:31,484 --> 00:10:33,524
That has been his dream
since forever.

235
00:10:34,383 --> 00:10:37,093
And that's why when you
invited him to Brazil,

236
00:10:37,118 --> 00:10:38,708
he was really happy.

237
00:10:39,734 --> 00:10:40,774
I'm his mom.

238
00:10:41,024 --> 00:10:42,814
I want him to make
his dreams come true

239
00:10:42,934 --> 00:10:44,434
without any distractions,

240
00:10:44,434 --> 00:10:48,271
and when he does it,
I'll be very happy.

241
00:10:50,234 --> 00:10:52,064
Well done!
Good job, you guys!

242
00:10:52,434 --> 00:10:55,396
In three days, our trip to
Tokyo will finally arrive,

243
00:10:55,421 --> 00:10:56,461
but before that...

244
00:10:56,854 --> 00:11:00,274
I'll just name the new
captain of the team.

245
00:11:00,394 --> 00:11:01,434
-Huh?
-A new captain?

246
00:11:01,434 --> 00:11:02,644
What about Genzo?

247
00:11:02,774 --> 00:11:03,934
Unfortunately,

248
00:11:03,959 --> 00:11:06,289
he won't be able to play
because of his injury.

249
00:11:06,774 --> 00:11:09,484
And that's why I've decided
to name someone else

250
00:11:09,509 --> 00:11:10,839
to take his place.

251
00:11:11,894 --> 00:11:14,354
I know it will be difficult
without his support,

252
00:11:14,564 --> 00:11:17,434
but that doesn't mean that
we can't win without him.

253
00:11:17,434 --> 00:11:18,934
We're still a strong team.

254
00:11:20,184 --> 00:11:21,894
All right, listen up,
you guys!

255
00:11:22,301 --> 00:11:23,221
The new captain...

256
00:11:23,734 --> 00:11:25,394
of the Nankatsu team...

257
00:11:27,734 --> 00:11:29,024
is Tsubasa.

258
00:11:29,814 --> 00:11:31,564
Me? The new captain?

259
00:11:31,684 --> 00:11:32,554
-Great, man!
-Huh?

260
00:11:32,579 --> 00:11:33,659
Congratulations!

261
00:11:33,684 --> 00:11:34,814
Tsubasa, huh?

262
00:11:34,934 --> 00:11:37,064
I'm sure the atomosphere
will be much better.

263
00:11:37,290 --> 00:11:39,330
From now on,
the Nankatsu team

264
00:11:39,355 --> 00:11:41,354
will play the way
its new captain

265
00:11:41,379 --> 00:11:42,684
says we will play.

266
00:11:42,934 --> 00:11:43,644
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

267
00:11:43,765 --> 00:11:45,030
-Tsubasa...
-Huh?

268
00:11:45,064 --> 00:11:46,934
-Some words for the team.
-Sure!

269
00:11:52,212 --> 00:11:54,422
We'll be
the best team of them all!

270
00:11:54,596 --> 00:11:56,317
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

271
00:11:56,833 --> 00:11:59,370
We'll be back
with Captain Tsubasa.

272
00:12:05,065 --> 00:12:07,105
AFFILIATION: NANKATSU FC BIRTHDAY: JULY 28 HEIGHT: 145 CM WEIGHT: 39 KG BLOOD TYPE: A

273
00:12:08,675 --> 00:12:09,675
Mom!

274
00:12:10,018 --> 00:12:11,770
I was chosen as
the new captain!

275
00:12:11,795 --> 00:12:13,600
What? Captain?
Really?

276
00:12:13,625 --> 00:12:16,230
Yeah! I can't wait to tell
Roberto too!

277
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:17,400
Where is he, Mom?

278
00:12:17,768 --> 00:12:19,468
He went out
a while ago, son.

279
00:12:19,715 --> 00:12:22,045
Ugh... That sucks.

280
00:12:22,587 --> 00:12:24,797
Well, son,
now that you're captain,

281
00:12:24,822 --> 00:12:27,190
you'll have to do
even better than before!

282
00:12:27,215 --> 00:12:28,215
I will!

283
00:12:35,413 --> 00:12:37,623
At the end, the three
of them agree, but...

284
00:12:38,085 --> 00:12:40,255
why do I still doubt
myself about this?

285
00:12:40,930 --> 00:12:42,020
I was the one
that proposed

286
00:12:42,045 --> 00:12:43,375
Tsubasa come to
Brazil with me,

287
00:12:43,708 --> 00:12:44,708
then why am I...

288
00:12:45,350 --> 00:12:46,350
why am I...

289
00:12:46,375 --> 00:12:47,625
doubting this?

290
00:12:51,482 --> 00:12:54,402
The national tournament
is about to begin, Son.

291
00:12:54,981 --> 00:12:55,981
Good luck!

292
00:12:56,640 --> 00:12:58,600
Please take care of him,
Roberto.

293
00:12:58,625 --> 00:12:59,835
I'm counting on you.

294
00:13:02,925 --> 00:13:05,235
And finally,
the day had arrived.

295
00:13:05,260 --> 00:13:07,295
The Nankatsu team
embarks on their journey

296
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:10,255
to Tokyo City to play in
the national tournament.

297
00:13:11,175 --> 00:13:14,049
All right! I want you all to
cheer to our beloved team,

298
00:13:14,074 --> 00:13:14,799
the Nankatsu!

299
00:13:14,824 --> 00:13:18,400
Let's go! Let's go!
Win! Win! Win!

300
00:13:18,425 --> 00:13:19,425
-Let's go! Let's go!
-Let's go! Let's go!

301
00:13:19,638 --> 00:13:20,638
-You will win!
-You will win!

302
00:13:20,675 --> 00:13:21,675
-Hurray! Hurray!
-Hurray! Hurray!

303
00:13:21,700 --> 00:13:22,740
-You will win!
-You will win!

304
00:13:23,042 --> 00:13:24,977
What a good bye, huh?

305
00:13:25,030 --> 00:13:26,730
I didn't think they cared
so much about us.

306
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:29,150
Even your mom is here.
Take a look.

307
00:13:29,175 --> 00:13:30,665
-Go, Son! You can do it!
-Huh?

308
00:13:30,690 --> 00:13:31,480
You're the best!

309
00:13:31,505 --> 00:13:34,175
Genzo didn't even come
to say good bye.

310
00:13:34,335 --> 00:13:35,505
-Uh-huh.
-Hey!

311
00:13:35,530 --> 00:13:37,745
Don't get
so sentimental, okay?

312
00:13:38,425 --> 00:13:41,104
Genzo...
I will keep my promise.

313
00:13:41,215 --> 00:13:42,505
-Tsubasa!
-Huh?

314
00:13:42,625 --> 00:13:43,965
-Take care!
-Roberto...

315
00:13:43,990 --> 00:13:45,085
-Do you hear me?
-I will win

316
00:13:45,110 --> 00:13:46,085
the national tournament

317
00:13:46,215 --> 00:13:47,755
and I will go with you
to Brazil!

318
00:13:47,875 --> 00:13:48,875
I swear!

319
00:13:50,255 --> 00:13:52,295
Yeah, come on,
that was awesome!

320
00:13:52,613 --> 00:13:54,165
-Let's go! Let's go!
-Let's go! Let's go!

321
00:13:54,234 --> 00:13:56,344
-You will win!
-You will win!

322
00:13:57,597 --> 00:13:58,597
Tsubasa!

323
00:13:58,640 --> 00:13:59,850
Don't you worry!

324
00:13:59,875 --> 00:14:01,755
I'll be there soon!

325
00:14:08,247 --> 00:14:09,647
I'm counting on you guys.

326
00:14:10,856 --> 00:14:12,701
Please wait for me.

327
00:14:13,855 --> 00:14:16,395
TOKYO

328
00:14:16,420 --> 00:14:18,195
WANGAN SOCCER PARK

329
00:14:22,390 --> 00:14:24,060
We're finally here
to participate

330
00:14:24,190 --> 00:14:25,534
in the national tournament!

331
00:14:25,559 --> 00:14:27,559
Always so cheerful,
aren't you?

332
00:14:28,312 --> 00:14:29,732
So, everyone's here?

333
00:14:29,875 --> 00:14:31,205
I hope you didn't
forget anything

334
00:14:31,230 --> 00:14:32,690
because there's
no going back.

335
00:14:32,860 --> 00:14:34,400
Hey, wanna go and take
a look at the field?

336
00:14:34,425 --> 00:14:36,045
Yeah, but we have to
leave our stuff

337
00:14:36,070 --> 00:14:37,295
at the hotel first.

338
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:38,480
-Hey, you!
-Huh?

339
00:14:38,505 --> 00:14:40,111
What do you think
you two are doing?!

340
00:14:40,136 --> 00:14:41,176
-Huh?
-Huh?

341
00:14:41,585 --> 00:14:43,400
-Got it!
-What the hell?!

342
00:14:43,425 --> 00:14:45,175
Here it goes, Kazuo!

343
00:14:45,573 --> 00:14:46,925
Great pass, Masao!

344
00:14:47,615 --> 00:14:48,730
What's their deal?!

345
00:14:48,755 --> 00:14:50,085
-Are they crazy?!
-Here!

346
00:14:50,215 --> 00:14:53,215
They're passing the ball
between the train lanes!

347
00:14:53,674 --> 00:14:54,374
That was easy!

348
00:14:54,474 --> 00:14:55,474
-Hey!
-Huh?

349
00:14:55,545 --> 00:14:57,505
Don't do that!
It's dangerous!

350
00:14:57,625 --> 00:15:00,761
Jeez, these train guards
are so annoying!

351
00:15:01,265 --> 00:15:02,265
Excuse me.

352
00:15:03,190 --> 00:15:04,354
Masao!

353
00:15:04,719 --> 00:15:05,719
Great pass!

354
00:15:07,675 --> 00:15:09,675
Did you see?
They're twins!

355
00:15:09,795 --> 00:15:11,255
-Here!
-Got it!

356
00:15:11,850 --> 00:15:12,560
Here you go!

357
00:15:12,585 --> 00:15:14,255
Hey, listen, Kazuo!
Masao!

358
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:16,190
Come here!
We have to go now!

359
00:15:16,215 --> 00:15:18,835
Yeah!
Kazuo, we gotta go!

360
00:15:18,965 --> 00:15:21,770
Sure, but first,
one last time! Go!

361
00:15:21,795 --> 00:15:22,965
I got it!

362
00:15:23,175 --> 00:15:24,175
Huh?

363
00:15:24,610 --> 00:15:27,005
Are you also playing
in the tournament?

364
00:15:27,030 --> 00:15:27,690
Yeah.

365
00:15:27,715 --> 00:15:29,335
My brother Kazuo and I
as well.

366
00:15:29,465 --> 00:15:31,045
We are from Team Hanawa.

367
00:15:31,045 --> 00:15:32,295
Nice to meet you all.

368
00:15:32,701 --> 00:15:34,401
Masao, let's go already!

369
00:15:34,426 --> 00:15:35,346
Yeah!

370
00:15:36,186 --> 00:15:37,396
What's the deal with
those two?

371
00:15:37,421 --> 00:15:38,526
They are very weird.

372
00:15:38,900 --> 00:15:41,230
Weird, but also
very impressive.

373
00:15:41,458 --> 00:15:42,878
Yeah...
Yeah, they are.

374
00:15:43,375 --> 00:15:44,795
This is so exciting.

375
00:15:44,925 --> 00:15:47,999
There will be tons of
players that we don't know.

376
00:15:48,675 --> 00:15:50,625
We have to give it
our best effort!

377
00:15:52,925 --> 00:15:55,810
The National
Juvenile Tournament.

378
00:15:55,835 --> 00:15:57,295
An event where
the young talent

379
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:58,795
can showcase their worth

380
00:15:58,925 --> 00:16:01,085
against players from
across the country

381
00:16:01,110 --> 00:16:02,085
during the summer.

382
00:16:02,295 --> 00:16:04,625
48 teams participate
in the tournament,

383
00:16:04,650 --> 00:16:06,835
divided in blocks
of six teams

384
00:16:06,860 --> 00:16:09,499
to start the process
of elimination.

385
00:16:09,795 --> 00:16:12,122
The best teams
from each block

386
00:16:12,147 --> 00:16:13,270
will go on to the finals

387
00:16:13,295 --> 00:16:15,795
and only the best one
will win.

388
00:16:16,025 --> 00:16:18,440
JUVENILE NATIONAL SOCCER
TOURNAMENT TEAMS DRAW

389
00:16:18,465 --> 00:16:20,175
This is going to be a heck of a time.

390
00:16:20,996 --> 00:16:22,510
-Taro!
-Huh?

391
00:16:22,535 --> 00:16:23,575
Ah!

392
00:16:23,969 --> 00:16:25,849
Hikaru and all my friends!

393
00:16:25,874 --> 00:16:27,374
How have you been, friend?!

394
00:16:27,841 --> 00:16:30,711
I was surprised to see you
with the Nankatsu team.

395
00:16:31,066 --> 00:16:32,186
They are from
the Furano team

396
00:16:32,303 --> 00:16:33,473
and they were my teammates.

397
00:16:33,895 --> 00:16:34,895
Oh!

398
00:16:35,020 --> 00:16:36,980
My name is Hikaru Matsuyama.

399
00:16:37,247 --> 00:16:39,747
And he's our captain,
Tsubasa Ozora.

400
00:16:39,835 --> 00:16:40,925
Hi, nice to meet you!

401
00:16:41,350 --> 00:16:42,520
We finally meet...

402
00:16:42,545 --> 00:16:45,215
Taro has told me so much
about you, Tsubasa.

403
00:16:46,903 --> 00:16:48,823
We'll be rivals now, Hikaru.

404
00:16:49,005 --> 00:16:50,625
Yeah, we'll be rivals.

405
00:16:51,279 --> 00:16:53,600
Tsubasa! Hello!
How have you been?!

406
00:16:53,625 --> 00:16:56,255
-Hello!
-Quite the lady's man, huh?

407
00:16:56,789 --> 00:16:58,459
I'm so happy to see you.

408
00:16:59,044 --> 00:17:01,158
I want to introduce you
to our Captain.

409
00:17:01,542 --> 00:17:02,872
He is Jun Misugi.

410
00:17:03,051 --> 00:17:04,051
It's my pleasure.

411
00:17:04,459 --> 00:17:06,299
I'm the captain of
Team Mussahi.

412
00:17:06,779 --> 00:17:08,029
Nice to meet you, Jun.

413
00:17:08,054 --> 00:17:09,054
I'm Tsubasa.

414
00:17:09,312 --> 00:17:10,682
I can't wait to
compete with you

415
00:17:10,707 --> 00:17:12,127
on the field,
Tsubasa.

416
00:17:12,781 --> 00:17:14,940
What a pretty girl!

417
00:17:14,965 --> 00:17:17,976
Hey, you're from
the Nankatsu team, right?

418
00:17:18,242 --> 00:17:20,375
You're huge!

419
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:22,150
I heard Genzo Wakabayashi
is not playing.

420
00:17:22,175 --> 00:17:25,215
-Is it true?
-Yeah, I guess you're right.

421
00:17:25,722 --> 00:17:28,435
I'm Taichi Nakanishi
from Team Naniwa.

422
00:17:28,460 --> 00:17:30,570
If Genzo is not here,
then that means...

423
00:17:30,698 --> 00:17:32,125
...I'm the number one
goalkeeper

424
00:17:32,184 --> 00:17:34,409
of the whole tournament.

425
00:17:35,085 --> 00:17:36,085
Huh?

426
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:38,560
It's those kids
from before...

427
00:17:38,585 --> 00:17:40,190
If I remember correctly,

428
00:17:40,215 --> 00:17:42,505
they said they're from
the Hanawa team.

429
00:17:43,545 --> 00:17:45,215
It's Kojiro Hyuga!

430
00:17:45,255 --> 00:17:47,215
They are the Meiwa team.

431
00:17:48,005 --> 00:17:51,659
Tsubasa's rivals
have finally gathered!

432
00:17:56,417 --> 00:17:59,705
Now we'll begin the draw
for each block's teams.

433
00:17:59,730 --> 00:18:02,440
From Shizuoka prefecture,
Tsubasa Ozora,

434
00:18:02,465 --> 00:18:04,045
Captain of
the Nankatsu team.

435
00:18:04,175 --> 00:18:05,175
Yes!

436
00:18:09,091 --> 00:18:12,492
Nankatsu will be on Block 1, Slot "A."

437
00:18:12,517 --> 00:18:13,555
NANKATSU SC

438
00:18:13,580 --> 00:18:14,545
Wow!

439
00:18:14,729 --> 00:18:15,729
Great, Tsubasa!

440
00:18:15,754 --> 00:18:17,019
That's a great spot!

441
00:18:17,044 --> 00:18:19,728
We'll be on Block number 1
for sure!

442
00:18:24,045 --> 00:18:25,715
Why is he looking at us
like that?

443
00:18:25,740 --> 00:18:29,215
The Meiwa team will be
on Slot "B" from Block 1.

444
00:18:29,505 --> 00:18:31,085
That... That can't be!

445
00:18:31,215 --> 00:18:32,850
They are on
the same block as us!

446
00:18:32,875 --> 00:18:33,770
That means...

447
00:18:33,795 --> 00:18:35,835
We'll play against
Meiwa first?!

448
00:18:36,499 --> 00:18:38,129
I wasn't expecting that.

449
00:18:40,264 --> 00:18:42,474
I see the first match
is against the Meiwa.

450
00:18:42,812 --> 00:18:44,612
Yeah, but don't worry.

451
00:18:44,637 --> 00:18:46,477
You get better
so you can play with us

452
00:18:46,502 --> 00:18:48,587
at the finals, got it?

453
00:18:49,063 --> 00:18:49,893
Got it.

454
00:18:49,949 --> 00:18:51,069
You have to win.

455
00:18:51,312 --> 00:18:52,402
You must do it.

456
00:18:52,785 --> 00:18:54,695
We will, I promise.

457
00:18:56,541 --> 00:18:58,661
Genzo sounded really upset
on the phone.

458
00:18:59,310 --> 00:19:00,350
I can't believe it.

459
00:19:00,375 --> 00:19:02,465
I really wish I could play.

460
00:19:03,949 --> 00:19:05,069
But why?

461
00:19:05,965 --> 00:19:08,795
Why did they have to
go against them first?

462
00:19:11,147 --> 00:19:13,487
MEIWA
TEAM 3

463
00:19:14,512 --> 00:19:16,172
-Captain!
-Huh?

464
00:19:16,835 --> 00:19:18,909
Captain, this is yours.

465
00:19:20,045 --> 00:19:21,045
Humph.

466
00:19:21,511 --> 00:19:22,511
Here, you keep it.

467
00:19:22,536 --> 00:19:24,401
Sure, but why, Captain?

468
00:19:24,925 --> 00:19:26,085
I don't need it.

469
00:19:27,585 --> 00:19:28,675
Huh, okay.

470
00:19:31,471 --> 00:19:35,550
Oh! Please,
someone take us!

471
00:19:39,045 --> 00:19:41,125
Just forget it, Boss.
No one will come.

472
00:19:41,125 --> 00:19:43,085
That sucks.
We can't get a ride.

473
00:19:43,110 --> 00:19:45,448
Well, if that's the case...

474
00:19:45,915 --> 00:19:47,140
...then you must
sacrifice yourself

475
00:19:47,165 --> 00:19:48,600
and get hit by a car!

476
00:19:48,625 --> 00:19:49,785
That'll make them stop!

477
00:19:49,823 --> 00:19:51,335
-Are you crazy?!
-Are you crazy?!

478
00:19:52,315 --> 00:19:52,875
Huh?

479
00:19:52,875 --> 00:19:53,315
Huh?
TOKAIDO EXPRESS DELIVERY

480
00:19:53,315 --> 00:19:53,835
TOKAIDO EXPRESS DELIVERY

481
00:19:53,835 --> 00:19:54,995
TOKAIDO EXPRESS DELIVERY
Hey there, kids,

482
00:19:54,995 --> 00:19:55,228
Hey there, kids,

483
00:19:55,255 --> 00:19:56,905
do you need a ride somewhere?

484
00:19:56,930 --> 00:19:58,100
Yes! Thank you so much!

485
00:19:58,125 --> 00:19:59,255
We're heading to Tokyo, sir.

486
00:19:59,280 --> 00:20:02,268
That's perfect!
I'm heading there as well!

487
00:20:02,468 --> 00:20:03,888
What are you
waiting for? Hop on!

488
00:20:04,130 --> 00:20:05,130
Great!

489
00:20:05,321 --> 00:20:07,861
Hey, everyone!
We got a ride!

490
00:20:07,886 --> 00:20:09,006
-Yeah!
-Cool!

491
00:20:09,031 --> 00:20:10,661
We finally can
go see our friends!

492
00:20:10,686 --> 00:20:12,150
Hey, hold on!

493
00:20:12,175 --> 00:20:14,730
I can only take three kids
on this truck!

494
00:20:14,755 --> 00:20:15,755
What?

495
00:20:15,875 --> 00:20:17,715
But it's okay.
No worrieds.

496
00:20:17,740 --> 00:20:20,545
We truck drivers always
help those in need.

497
00:20:21,140 --> 00:20:23,730
Attention, all units,
I need back up.

498
00:20:23,755 --> 00:20:25,900
I'm in Nankatsu city.

499
00:20:26,030 --> 00:20:27,480
The cargo is
elementary kids

500
00:20:27,505 --> 00:20:29,040
that need to go and
support their friends.

501
00:20:29,065 --> 00:20:30,065
-Please hurry, over!

502
00:20:30,465 --> 00:20:31,465
-Huh?
-Huh?

503
00:20:36,409 --> 00:20:38,459
-Wow!
-Unbelievable!

504
00:20:38,484 --> 00:20:40,864
Well, you need to
get in already!

505
00:20:44,125 --> 00:20:46,085
Sir, thank you
very much for everything.

506
00:20:46,310 --> 00:20:48,060
So tell me,
why are you going to Tokyo?

507
00:20:48,180 --> 00:20:49,520
We're going to
a soccer match.

508
00:20:49,545 --> 00:20:50,255
Soccer?

509
00:20:50,375 --> 00:20:52,245
So you're the cheerleaders
or what?

510
00:20:52,270 --> 00:20:52,850
That's right.

511
00:20:52,875 --> 00:20:53,925
Oh I get it.

512
00:20:54,045 --> 00:20:56,270
I also like soccer a lot.

513
00:20:56,295 --> 00:20:58,085
Huh?
Hold on, young lady,

514
00:20:58,110 --> 00:20:59,810
if you had been
a team manager,

515
00:20:59,835 --> 00:21:01,932
you'd gone with them, right?

516
00:21:03,039 --> 00:21:04,629
It's best not to
mention that, sir!

517
00:21:04,654 --> 00:21:05,734
Huh?

518
00:21:06,230 --> 00:21:08,100
We don't need
a team manager.

519
00:21:08,125 --> 00:21:09,965
It's all because of
that coach.

520
00:21:10,085 --> 00:21:12,045
How dares he tell me
they don't need me!?

521
00:21:12,175 --> 00:21:15,480
Oh well! I'll just go and
cheer the team!

522
00:21:15,505 --> 00:21:17,965
And Tsubasa!

523
00:21:22,690 --> 00:21:24,392
And now,
we present you the teams.

524
00:21:24,642 --> 00:21:25,350
FURANO SOCCER CLUB
HOKKAIDO

525
00:21:25,375 --> 00:21:26,600
Yes. This year's

526
00:21:26,625 --> 00:21:29,880
National Juvenile Tournament
is about to begin.

527
00:21:30,005 --> 00:21:31,989
Teams from the North
and South of Japan

528
00:21:32,014 --> 00:21:34,224
have earned their place
to be here.

529
00:21:34,249 --> 00:21:37,770
48 teams in total divided
into different blocks.

530
00:21:37,795 --> 00:21:38,585
All of them will compete

531
00:21:38,610 --> 00:21:40,375
during the following
six days.

532
00:21:41,046 --> 00:21:43,966
I'm sure we will witness
some marvelous talent

533
00:21:43,991 --> 00:21:46,371
that will no doubt shine
on the soccer field!

534
00:21:46,435 --> 00:21:47,105
MIEWA FC
SAITAMA

535
00:21:47,185 --> 00:21:49,456
NANKATSU SC SHIZUOKA

536
00:21:49,481 --> 00:21:50,789
We're finally here.

537
00:21:50,814 --> 00:21:52,404
The national tournament.

538
00:21:55,520 --> 00:21:57,100
And now,
the Captain

539
00:21:57,125 --> 00:21:59,843
from the Nankatsu team,
Tsubasa Ozora,

540
00:21:59,868 --> 00:22:01,158
will say a few words.

541
00:22:05,045 --> 00:22:06,125
Players!

542
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:07,600
Let's play this tournament

543
00:22:07,625 --> 00:22:10,255
with honor and respect
of our competing rivals!

544
00:22:10,659 --> 00:22:13,529
Let's play with passion and
a spirit of sportsmanship!

545
00:22:14,255 --> 00:22:16,925
I'm here representing
Nankatsu, and my name is...

546
00:22:17,216 --> 00:22:18,676
Tsubasa Ozora!

547
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:24,230
Yeah!
Well said, sweetie!

548
00:22:24,255 --> 00:22:26,215
Did you like what he said,
Roberto?

549
00:22:26,455 --> 00:22:27,455
I did!

550
00:22:31,875 --> 00:22:33,465
Sportsmanship...

551
00:22:35,655 --> 00:22:40,655
[ending theme]
